{
  "video_id": "C2p42GASnUo",
  "title": "Poetry, music and identity (with English subtitles) | Jorge Drexler",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13180.0,
      "end_time": 15215.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to tell you the story of a song."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15684.0,
      "end_time": 20780.0,
      "text": "I was in Madrid one night in 2002"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20102.0,
      "end_time": 22405.0,
      "text": "with my teacher and friend Joaquín Sabina,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22429.0,
      "end_time": 24506.0,
      "text": "when he said he had something to give me."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25419.0,
      "end_time": 26761.0,
      "text": "He said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26785.0,
      "end_time": 30142.0,
      "text": "\"Jorge, I have some lines that you need to put into a song."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30166.0,
      "end_time": 31825.0,
      "text": "Take these down, take these down.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 31849.0,
      "end_time": 34853.0,
      "text": "I looked on the table but all I found was a circular coaster,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34877.0,
      "end_time": 37229.0,
      "text": "on which I wrote the lines my teacher dictated."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 37253.0,
      "end_time": 39726.0,
      "text": "They were four lines that went like this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39750.0,
      "end_time": 43870.0,
      "text": "\"I am a Jewish Moor living among Christians"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 43111.0,
      "end_time": 46799.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know who my God is, nor who my brothers are.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 48177.0,
      "end_time": 51198.0,
      "text": "Those lines really made an impression on me."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 51222.0,
      "end_time": 54206.0,
      "text": "I said, \"What beautiful lyrics, Joaquín. Did you write them?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 54230.0,
      "end_time": 59708.0,
      "text": "He said no, they were by another composer named Chicho Sánchez Ferlosio,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 59732.0,
      "end_time": 62563.0,
      "text": "who was less known than Joaquín, but also a great poet."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 63552.0,
      "end_time": 65111.0,
      "text": "These lines came to me at a time"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65135.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67942.0,
      "text": "where I had been wanting to express something for a while,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 67966.0,
      "end_time": 69606.0,
      "text": "but didn&#39;t quite know how."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 69630.0,
      "end_time": 72515.0,
      "text": "I was getting up to leave and go home to write,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72540.0,
      "end_time": 75300.0,
      "text": "when Joaquín stopped me and said, \"Hang on, hang on,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 75540.0,
      "end_time": 76964.0,
      "text": "and presented me with this challenge:"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 77802.0,
      "end_time": 80797.0,
      "text": "\"Write the stanzas for this song"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 80821.0,
      "end_time": 82360.0,
      "text": "in Décimas.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 82906.0,
      "end_time": 85397.0,
      "text": "Now, at this point in my life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 85421.0,
      "end_time": 88169.0,
      "text": "I still wasn&#39;t completely sure what Décimas were,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 89217.0,
      "end_time": 93479.0,
      "text": "but I was too embarrassed to tell my teacher I didn&#39;t know."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 93503.0,
      "end_time": 97188.0,
      "text": "So I put on my best \"Yeah, I totally understand\" face,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 97212.0,
      "end_time": 99951.0,
      "text": "and went home to look up what Décimas were."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 99975.0,
      "end_time": 103455.0,
      "text": "I learned that a Décima is a type of verse"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 103479.0,
      "end_time": 104894.0,
      "text": "that only exists in Spanish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 104918.0,
      "end_time": 106182.0,
      "text": "and that it has 10 lines."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 106206.0,
      "end_time": 108207.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s very, very complex --"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 108231.0,
      "end_time": 111401.0,
      "text": "perhaps the most complex style of stanza that we have in Spanish."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 111425.0,
      "end_time": 113884.0,
      "text": "It also has a very concrete date of origin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 113908.0,
      "end_time": 116242.0,
      "text": "which is very rare for a style of stanza."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 116266.0,
      "end_time": 119921.0,
      "text": "The Décima was invented in Spain in 1591,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 121513.0,
      "end_time": 125836.0,
      "text": "by a guy named Vicente Espinel, a musician and poet from Málaga."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 127268.0,
      "end_time": 129887.0,
      "text": "And listen to this coincidence: he was the same guy"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 130741.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132434.0,
      "text": "who added the sixth string"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 132458.0,
      "end_time": 134761.0,
      "text": "to what would later be called the Spanish guitar."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 134785.0,
      "end_time": 136151.0,
      "text": "This string right here --"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 136175.0,
      "end_time": 137468.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s called the \"bordona.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 138424.0,
      "end_time": 141868.0,
      "text": "From Spain, the Décima, with its 10 lines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 141892.0,
      "end_time": 146698.0,
      "text": "crosses over to America, just like the Spanish guitar,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 146723.0,
      "end_time": 148253.0,
      "text": "but in contrast to the Décima,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 148277.0,
      "end_time": 150726.0,
      "text": "the Spanish guitar continues to live today"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 150750.0,
      "end_time": 152439.0,
      "text": "on both sides of the Atlantic."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 152463.0,
      "end_time": 155555.0,
      "text": "But the Décima, in Spain, its birthplace,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 155579.0,
      "end_time": 157112.0,
      "text": "disappeared; it died out."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 158330.0,
      "end_time": 160351.0,
      "text": "It died out about 200 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 160376.0,
      "end_time": 165400.0,
      "text": "and yet in Latin America, from Mexico to Chile,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 165640.0,
      "end_time": 168284.0,
      "text": "all our countries maintain some form of the Décima"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 169420.0,
      "end_time": 170575.0,
      "text": "in our popular traditions."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 172151.0,
      "end_time": 174465.0,
      "text": "In each place, they&#39;ve given it a different name,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 174489.0,
      "end_time": 176200.0,
      "text": "and set it to different music."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 176576.0,
      "end_time": 180900.0,
      "text": "It has a lot of different names -- more than 20 in total on the continent."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 181535.0,
      "end_time": 184629.0,
      "text": "In Mexico, for example, it&#39;s called the \"Son Jarocho,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 184653.0,
      "end_time": 186458.0,
      "text": "\"Canto de mejorana\" in Panama;"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 186482.0,
      "end_time": 188360.0,
      "text": "\"Galerón\" in Venezuela;"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 188600.0,
      "end_time": 189960.0,
      "text": "\"Payada\" in Uruguay and Argentina;"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 191117.0,
      "end_time": 192530.0,
      "text": "\"Repentismo\" in Cuba."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 192555.0,
      "end_time": 194837.0,
      "text": "In Peru, they call it the Peruvian Décima,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 194861.0,
      "end_time": 197959.0,
      "text": "because the Décima becomes so integrated into our traditions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 197984.0,
      "end_time": 201517.0,
      "text": "that if someone asks, people from each place are completely convinced"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 201541.0,
      "end_time": 204296.0,
      "text": "that the Décima was invented in their country."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 204320.0,
      "end_time": 205668.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 205693.0,
      "end_time": 207844.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s also got a really surprising feature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 207868.0,
      "end_time": 211137.0,
      "text": "which is that despite the fact that it developed independently"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 211161.0,
      "end_time": 213198.0,
      "text": "in each of the different countries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 213222.0,
      "end_time": 217600.0,
      "text": "it maintains even today, 400 years after its creation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 217624.0,
      "end_time": 224690.0,
      "text": "exactly the same rhyme, syllable and line structure --"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 224816.0,
      "end_time": 228523.0,
      "text": "the same structure Vicente Espinel gave it during the Spanish Baroque period."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 228547.0,
      "end_time": 229728.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the structure --"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 229752.0,
      "end_time": 232778.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll give you the basic idea and then later you can look online"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 232802.0,
      "end_time": 234922.0,
      "text": "and learn more about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 234946.0,
      "end_time": 238110.0,
      "text": "The Décima is ten lines long; each line has eight syllables."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 239781.0,
      "end_time": 242256.0,
      "text": "The first line rhymes with the fourth and the fifth;"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 242280.0,
      "end_time": 243828.0,
      "text": "the second line, with the third;"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 243852.0,
      "end_time": 246659.0,
      "text": "the sixth line, with the seventh and the tenth;"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 246683.0,
      "end_time": 249117.0,
      "text": "and the eighth line rhymes with the ninth."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 249141.0,
      "end_time": 251928.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a bit complicated, to be honest."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 251952.0,
      "end_time": 254971.0,
      "text": "And me -- imagine me, trying to write in Décimas."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 256269.99999999997,
      "end_time": 257968.99999999997,
      "text": "But it&#39;s not as complicated as it seems."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 258882.0,
      "end_time": 262430.0,
      "text": "Plus, it&#39;s amazing that it&#39;s survived with the same structure"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 262670.0,
      "end_time": 263659.0,
      "text": "for more than four centuries."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 264680.0,
      "end_time": 268152.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not that complicated, because it has an impressive musicality to it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 268176.0,
      "end_time": 269582.0,
      "text": "a type of musicality"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 270616.0,
      "end_time": 273421.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s very hard to describe technically."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 273916.0,
      "end_time": 275509.0,
      "text": "I prefer that you listen to it."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 275533.0,
      "end_time": 278359.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;m going to recite a Décima,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 279102.0,
      "end_time": 282943.0,
      "text": "one of the Décimas that I wrote for this song."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 284940.0,
      "end_time": 288916.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to ask that you concentrate just on the musicality of the rhymes."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 289932.0,
      "end_time": 291849.0,
      "text": "For those of you with headphones on --"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 291873.0,
      "end_time": 296635.0,
      "text": "I see that some of you are listening to the translation --"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 297512.0,
      "end_time": 299577.0,
      "text": "please take them off for a minute."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 299601.0,
      "end_time": 302183.0,
      "text": "(English) Take your headphones off, it you have them."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 303228.0,
      "end_time": 309245.0,
      "text": "(English) Forget about the meaning of the words for a few seconds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 309269.0,
      "end_time": 311240.0,
      "text": "(English) and then you&#39;ll put them back."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 311264.0,
      "end_time": 313700.0,
      "text": "(English) Forget about the structure."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 313940.0,
      "end_time": 314882.0,
      "text": "(Spanish) Forget about the structure."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 314906.0,
      "end_time": 320148.0,
      "text": "(English) And just ... it&#39;s all about the choreography of sound of the Décima."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 320172.0,
      "end_time": 322429.0,
      "text": "(Spanish) A choreography of sound."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 324572.0,
      "end_time": 327978.0,
      "text": "(Sings in Spanish) \"There is not one death that does not cause me pain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 328800.0,
      "end_time": 329190.0,
      "text": "there are no winners,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 329690.0,
      "end_time": 331987.0,
      "text": "here’s nothing but suffering and another life blown away."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 332110.0,
      "end_time": 335388.0,
      "text": "War is a terrible school no matter what the disguise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 335412.0,
      "end_time": 338310.0,
      "text": "forgive me for not enlisting under any flag,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 338334.0,
      "end_time": 343211.0,
      "text": "any daydream is worth more than a sad piece of cloth.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 345841.0,
      "end_time": 347436.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a Décima."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 347971.0,
      "end_time": 350278.0,
      "text": "(English) You can put your headphones back on."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 350302.0,
      "end_time": 351380.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 351404.0,
      "end_time": 352557.0,
      "text": "(English) Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 352581.0,
      "end_time": 355683.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 357176.0,
      "end_time": 360474.0,
      "text": "I also applaud Vicente Espinel, because here it is 426 years later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 360499.0,
      "end_time": 362226.0,
      "text": "and the Décima lives on everywhere"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 362250.0,
      "end_time": 363448.0,
      "text": "in its original state."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 363472.0,
      "end_time": 366720.0,
      "text": "I wrote three like that one; you just heard the second."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 366960.0,
      "end_time": 368770.0,
      "text": "I wrote the first one having only recently learned how,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 368794.0,
      "end_time": 370899.0,
      "text": "and it has some errors in terms of meter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 370923.0,
      "end_time": 373880.0,
      "text": "so it&#39;s not presentable in its current state."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 373112.0,
      "end_time": 375731.0,
      "text": "But the one I sang was good, more or less."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 375755.0,
      "end_time": 378683.0,
      "text": "So: What was it about?"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 379292.0,
      "end_time": 381510.0,
      "text": "What was the meaning behind those lines?"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 381534.0,
      "end_time": 385570.0,
      "text": "I had just returned from doing a concert in Israel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 385993.0,
      "end_time": 389710.0,
      "text": "and I was very emotional over a problem that hits really close to home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 389734.0,
      "end_time": 391801.0,
      "text": "which is the Israeli-Palestinian conflict."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 391825.0,
      "end_time": 393948.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll explain: my dad&#39;s family is Jewish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 393972.0,
      "end_time": 396844.0,
      "text": "and my mom&#39;s family are non-practicing Christians."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 396869.0,
      "end_time": 401428.0,
      "text": "I was raised in a home where the two traditions lived together"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 401452.0,
      "end_time": 403164.0,
      "text": "more or less in harmony."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 404608.0,
      "end_time": 408395.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t unusual to see my Jewish grandpa dressed as Santa Claus, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 408419.0,
      "end_time": 411657.0,
      "text": "or to see my non-Jewish grandpa at the synagogue wearing his kippah,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 411681.0,
      "end_time": 415960.0,
      "text": "at family celebrations, wearing the same expression that I probably had"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 415120.0,
      "end_time": 416483.0,
      "text": "when Sabina told me --"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 416507.0,
      "end_time": 417547.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 417571.0,
      "end_time": 419633.0,
      "text": "that he had some Décima lines for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 421986.0,
      "end_time": 425616.0,
      "text": "For someone raised in that kind of environment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 425641.0,
      "end_time": 430852.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s especially painful to see the difficulty the opposing parties have"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 430876.0,
      "end_time": 434630.0,
      "text": "in putting themselves in the other side&#39;s shoes even for a moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 434870.0,
      "end_time": 435637.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s what I wrote about."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 436223.0,
      "end_time": 437473.0,
      "text": "I already had the lyrics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 437497.0,
      "end_time": 439946.0,
      "text": "I had the form -- the Décima -- and the content."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 440947.0,
      "end_time": 442806.0,
      "text": "I needed to write the music."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 443960.0,
      "end_time": 445390.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll give you some context."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 445414.0,
      "end_time": 449233.0,
      "text": "I had only recently moved from Uruguay, where I&#39;m from, to Spain."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 450113.0,
      "end_time": 452935.0,
      "text": "And I was feeling very raw with nostalgia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 452959.0,
      "end_time": 455739.0,
      "text": "like many of you here, who are away from home."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 456910.0,
      "end_time": 460360.0,
      "text": "And I wanted my song to be very, very Uruguayan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 460384.0,
      "end_time": 463173.0,
      "text": "the most Uruguayan type of song there is -- the milonga."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 464130.0,
      "end_time": 468272.0,
      "text": "So now, I had been studying the Décima, and after finding out"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 469643.0,
      "end_time": 472203.0,
      "text": "that everyone tried to claim the Décima as their own,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 472227.0,
      "end_time": 474940.0,
      "text": "that it was invented in their country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 474119.0,
      "end_time": 475273.0,
      "text": "it made me wonder:"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 475297.0,
      "end_time": 477912.0,
      "text": "What does it mean when we say the milonga is Uruguayan?"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 477936.0,
      "end_time": 483553.0,
      "text": "The milonga has a rhythmic pattern that we musicians call 3-3-2."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 484130.0,
      "end_time": 487439.0,
      "text": "(Counts out the beats) One two three, one two three, one two."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 491738.0,
      "end_time": 494239.0,
      "text": "And it has a characteristic emphasis."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 494263.0,
      "end_time": 497135.0,
      "text": "(Sings)"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 502744.0,
      "end_time": 505475.0,
      "text": "But this characteristic rhythm pattern"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 505499.0,
      "end_time": 506930.0,
      "text": "comes from Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 507400.0,
      "end_time": 510510.0,
      "text": "In the ninth century you could find it in the brothels of Persia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 510534.0,
      "end_time": 511693.0,
      "text": "and in the thirteenth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 513150.0,
      "end_time": 515813.0,
      "text": "in Spain, from where, five centuries later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 515837.0,
      "end_time": 518487.0,
      "text": "it would cross over to America with the African slaves."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 519697.0,
      "end_time": 524730.0,
      "text": "Meanwhile, in the Balkans, it encounters the Roma scale --"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 524970.0,
      "end_time": 526957.0,
      "text": "(Sings)"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 531389.0,
      "end_time": 534147.0,
      "text": "which in part, gives birth to klezmer music,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 534902.0,
      "end_time": 539220.0,
      "text": "which Ukrainian Jewish immigrants bring to Brooklyn, New York."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 539668.0,
      "end_time": 541480.0,
      "text": "They sing it in their banquet halls."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 542531.0,
      "end_time": 548151.0,
      "text": "(Sings \"Hava Nagila\")"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 549305.0,
      "end_time": 552231.0,
      "text": "And their neighbor, an Argentine kid of Italian origin"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 552255.0,
      "end_time": 554521.0,
      "text": "named Astor Piazzolla,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 554545.0,
      "end_time": 556563.0,
      "text": "hears it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 556587.0,
      "end_time": 558114.0,
      "text": "assimilates it"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 558138.0,
      "end_time": 561139.0,
      "text": "and transforms the tango of the second half of the 20th century"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 561163.0,
      "end_time": 562316.0,
      "text": "with his ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 562340.0,
      "end_time": 565443.0,
      "text": "(Counts out the beats) One two three, one two three, one two."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 565845.0,
      "end_time": 568768.0,
      "text": "(Sings \"Adios Nonino\")"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 573934.0,
      "end_time": 578625.0,
      "text": "He also played it on his bandoneon, a 19th-century German instrument"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 578649.0,
      "end_time": 582776.0,
      "text": "created for churches that couldn&#39;t afford to buy organs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 582800.0,
      "end_time": 585166.0,
      "text": "and that ends up, incredibly, in Río de la Plata,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 585191.0,
      "end_time": 589278.0,
      "text": "forming the very essence of the tango and the milonga,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 589302.0,
      "end_time": 593268.0,
      "text": "in the very same way another instrument just as important as the bandoneon did:"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 594345.0,
      "end_time": 595896.0,
      "text": "the Spanish guitar."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 595920.0,
      "end_time": 599310.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 608277.0,
      "end_time": 611101.0,
      "text": "To which, by the way, Vicente Espinel, in the 16th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 611125.0,
      "end_time": 612377.0,
      "text": "added a sixth string."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 612401.0,
      "end_time": 615271.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s amazing how all these things are coming full circle."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 615295.0,
      "end_time": 618175.0,
      "text": "What have I learned in these 15 years since the song was born"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 618199.0,
      "end_time": 621535.0,
      "text": "from going all over the world with four lines written on a coaster"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 621559.0,
      "end_time": 622709.0,
      "text": "from a bar in Madrid?"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 624373.0,
      "end_time": 625664.0,
      "text": "That Décimas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 626511.0,
      "end_time": 627751.0,
      "text": "the milonga,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 627775.0,
      "end_time": 629341.0,
      "text": "songs, people --"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 630281.0,
      "end_time": 632233.0,
      "text": "the closer you get to them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 632258.0,
      "end_time": 634758.0,
      "text": "the more complex their identity becomes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 635425.0,
      "end_time": 637479.0,
      "text": "and the more nuances and details appear."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 638638.0,
      "end_time": 641787.0,
      "text": "I learned that identity is infinitely dense,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 641811.0,
      "end_time": 644363.0,
      "text": "like an infinite series of real numbers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 644387.0,
      "end_time": 646135.0,
      "text": "and that even if you get very close"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 646159.0,
      "end_time": 647317.0,
      "text": "and zoom in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 647341.0,
      "end_time": 648492.0,
      "text": "it never ends."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 650287.0,
      "end_time": 654860.0,
      "text": "Before I sing you a song and say goodbye,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 654884.0,
      "end_time": 657158.0,
      "text": "allow me to tell you one last story."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 657182.0,
      "end_time": 661782.0,
      "text": "Not long ago, we were in Mexico after a concert."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 662722.0,
      "end_time": 664983.0,
      "text": "And since the concert promoters know me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 665700.0,
      "end_time": 668930.0,
      "text": "they knew I was a Décima freak and that everywhere I go I ask about it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 668955.0,
      "end_time": 670693.0,
      "text": "insisting on hearing Décima artists."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 670717.0,
      "end_time": 675407.0,
      "text": "So they organized a son jarocho show for me at their house."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 675916.0,
      "end_time": 680531.0,
      "text": "If you recall, the son jarocho is one of the styles of music"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 680555.0,
      "end_time": 682646.0,
      "text": "that uses Décimas in its verses."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 684372.0,
      "end_time": 688184.0,
      "text": "When these amazing musicians finished playing"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 688208.0,
      "end_time": 691860.0,
      "text": "what is for me, something amazing, which is the son jarocho,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 691110.0,
      "end_time": 692775.0,
      "text": "they finished playing and were ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 692799.0,
      "end_time": 695180.0,
      "text": "I went up to greet them, really excited,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 695420.0,
      "end_time": 699286.0,
      "text": "getting ready to thank them for their gift of music,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 699310.0,
      "end_time": 701539.0,
      "text": "and this young kid says to me --"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 703263.0,
      "end_time": 706133.0,
      "text": "and he says it with the best of intentions -- he says,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 706157.0,
      "end_time": 713121.0,
      "text": "\"We&#39;re very proud, sir, to be keeping alive the purest origins"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 713145.0,
      "end_time": 715403.0,
      "text": "of our Mexican identity.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 716238.0,
      "end_time": 719154.0,
      "text": "And to tell you the truth, I didn&#39;t really know what to say."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 719178.0,
      "end_time": 720207.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 720231.0,
      "end_time": 723396.0,
      "text": "I stood there looking at him. I gave him a hug and left, but ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 723420.0,
      "end_time": 724685.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 724710.0,
      "end_time": 726695.0,
      "text": "But he was right, too, though. Right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 726719.0,
      "end_time": 729550.0,
      "text": "In reality, the Décima is its origin, but at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 729574.0,
      "end_time": 731944.0,
      "text": "just like in the milonga and in the Décima,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 731968.0,
      "end_time": 735915.0,
      "text": "are the roots of many more cultures from all over the place, like he said."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 737833.0,
      "end_time": 741510.0,
      "text": "Later, when I got back to the hotel, I thought about it for a while."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 741534.0,
      "end_time": 742700.0,
      "text": "And I thought:"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 742724.0,
      "end_time": 745628.0,
      "text": "things only look pure"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 746913.0,
      "end_time": 749880.0,
      "text": "if you look at them from far away."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 749861.0,
      "end_time": 753206.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s very important to know about our roots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 753230.0,
      "end_time": 757252.0,
      "text": "to know where we come from, to understand our history."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 757276.0,
      "end_time": 760274.0,
      "text": "But at the same time, as important as knowing where we&#39;re from,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 760298.0,
      "end_time": 763874.0,
      "text": "is understanding that deep down,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 763898.0,
      "end_time": 765858.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re all from nowhere"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 765882.0,
      "end_time": 767507.0,
      "text": "and a little bit from everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 767531.0,
      "end_time": 768756.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 768780.0,
      "end_time": 771908.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 778300.0,
      "end_time": 780241.0,
      "text": "This is \"The milonga of the Jewish Moor.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 781998.0,
      "end_time": 785282.0,
      "text": "(Music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 794456.0,
      "end_time": 796457.0,
      "text": "(Sings)"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 796481.0,
      "end_time": 801668.0,
      "text": "For every wall a lament in Jerusalem the golden"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 804560.0,
      "end_time": 809883.0,
      "text": "and 100 wasted lives for every commandment."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 811356.0,
      "end_time": 817660.0,
      "text": "I am dust in your wind and although I bleed through your wound,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 818867.0,
      "end_time": 824533.0,
      "text": "and every beloved stone has my deepest affection,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 825568.0,
      "end_time": 831864.0,
      "text": "there is not a stone in the world worth more than a human life."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 834311.0,
      "end_time": 841247.0,
      "text": "I am a Jewish Moor who lives among Christians"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 841654.0,
      "end_time": 848518.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know who my God is, nor who my brothers are."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 850310.0,
      "end_time": 856301.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know who my God is, nor who my brothers are."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 859479.0,
      "end_time": 865100.0,
      "text": "There is not one death that does not cause me pain, there are no winners"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 866840.0,
      "end_time": 872862.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s nothing but suffering and another life blown away."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 874316.0,
      "end_time": 880130.0,
      "text": "War is a terrible school no matter what the disguise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 881682.0,
      "end_time": 887214.0,
      "text": "forgive me for not enlisting under any flag,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 888351.0,
      "end_time": 895248.0,
      "text": "any daydream is worth more than a sad piece of cloth."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 896946.0,
      "end_time": 903781.0,
      "text": "I am a Jewish Moor who lives among Christians"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 904162.0,
      "end_time": 910902.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know who my God is, nor who my brothers are."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 912331.0,
      "end_time": 918507.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know who my God is, nor who my brothers are."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 925678.0,
      "end_time": 930679.0,
      "text": "And nobody has my permission for killing in my name,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 932963.0,
      "end_time": 939122.0,
      "text": "a man is but a man and if there is a God, this was his wish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 940360.0,
      "end_time": 946294.0,
      "text": "the very ground I tread will live on, once I am gone"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 947732.0,
      "end_time": 953461.0,
      "text": "on my way to oblivion, and all doctrines will suffer the same fate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 953946.0,
      "end_time": 958943.0,
      "text": "and there is not one nation that has not proclaimed itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
